[ ] CLI output projects by shape and destination $Decision 2026-07-21: index, tree, and graph are portable SPARQL query families and consumer guarantees, not per-query metadata or a custom query language. Family directory placement opts a complete .sparql file into validation and shape-aware presentation; raw/named queries remain unrestricted, and aggregates remain ordinary SELECT rows. The index slice now validates the existing contract, defaults pipes to NDJSON, supports explicit table/json/ndjson/jsonld, emits structured empty results, and clearhead.nvim requests JSON-LD explicitly. Remaining work: prove tree with the first parent-linked SELECT consumer, then graph with the first standard CONSTRUCT query and RDF serialization; keep both runnable unchanged in external SPARQL tooling.$ !2 #019f76ca-f3b1-7613-a0de-74f453f8576c
